SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 127
BY SENATOR KLEINPETER
COMMENDATIONS. Commends Jensen LeBlanc for being named a Children's Miracle
Network National Champion.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Addis, Louisiana resident Jensen LeBlanc upon being named a Children's
3 Miracle Network National Champion and to recognize his courage, perseverance,
4 and inspiring impact on others.
5 WHEREAS, Jensen LeBlanc, an eleven-year-old resident of Addis, Louisiana, has
6 been selected as a National Champion for Children's Miracle Network Hospitals, one of only
7 twenty children nationwide chosen to serve as ambassadors for children treated at member
8 hospitals across the United States; and
9 WHEREAS, Jensen was diagnosed at just seven months old with croup and stridor,
10 a rare condition that makes breathing difficult, and has endured significant medical
11 challenges from an early age; and
12 WHEREAS, through his treatment journey at Our Lady of the Lake Children's
13 Hospital, Jensen demonstrated extraordinary resilience and positivity, previously being
14 named a local Children's Miracle Network Champion in both 2023 and 2024 before
15 advancing to the national level; and
16 WHEREAS, Jensen's outlook on life, marked by optimism and a determination to
17 make the best of difficult circumstances, has inspired medical professionals, community
18 leaders, and all who have encountered his story; and
