1 WHEREAS, in recognition of his achievement and character, officials in both East
2 Baton Rouge Parish and West Baton Rouge Parish proclaimed February 23, 2026, as "Jensen
3 LeBlanc Day," and he was presented with a key to the town of Addis by Mayor David
4 Toups; and
5 WHEREAS, Jensen has embraced his role as a national ambassador by sharing his
6 story to inspire other children facing medical adversity and by promoting support for
7 children's hospitals; and
8 WHEREAS, Jensen aspires to become a pediatric surgeon and give back by helping
9 children facing challenges similar to his own; and
10 WHEREAS, Jensen LeBlanc's courage, compassion, and leadership reflect great
11 credit upon himself, his family, his community, and the state of Louisiana and should serve
12 as an inspiration to us all.
13 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
14 does hereby commend Jensen LeBlanc upon being named a Children's Miracle Network
15 National Champion and does hereby express sincere appreciation for his courage,
16 determination, and inspirational leadership.
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
18 Jensen LeBlanc and his family as an expression of the Senate's admiration and best wishes
19 for continued success and good health.
